The paper deals with the routing of messages in vehicular networks, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The proposed solution involves fog computing, which is a subfield of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also addresses issues related to system dynamics and control, which is a subfield of systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses security and privacy concerns related to message dissemination, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper proposes a novel approach for message dissemination using fog computing, which involves optimization and resource allocation, which is a subfield of information theory (cs.IT).
